author: boston.com
title: Multi-car crash closes two lanes on Mass. Pike - News
text:
All lanes on the Mass. Pike westbound outside the Prudential Tunnel have been reopened, according to a Mass. State Police spokesman. Two lanes were closed earlier Tuesday due to a three-car crash.
#MAtraffic , Rte 90 WB at the end of the Pru Tunnel, all lanes open from earlier crash.
— Mass State Police (@MassStatePolice) October 13, 2015 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below State police said the occupant of one of the cars was transported to the hospital for minor injuries.
#MAtraffic 2 left lanes closed, Rte 90 WB just outside Pru Tunnel in #Boston , due to 3 car crash. Minor injuries.
— Mass State Police (@MassStatePolice) October 13, 2015
